Greywolf Capital Management LP Decreased Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (HMHC) Holding, FREESEAS ORD (FREEF) Sellers Increased By 160.27% Their Shorts


					
						July 24, 2017 - By Linda Rogers

 FREESEAS ORD (OTCMKTS:FREEF) had an increase of 160.27% in short interest. FREEF’s SI was 57,000 shares in July as released by FINRA. Its up 160.27% from 21,900 shares previously. About 184,008 shares traded. FreeSeas Inc (OTCMKTS:FREEF) has 0.00% since July 24, 2016 and is . It has underperformed by 16.70% the S&P500.







Greywolf Capital Management Lp decreased Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (HMHC) stake by 29.67% reported in 2016Q4 SEC filing. Greywolf Capital Management Lp sold 928,911 shares as Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (HMHC)’s stock rose 9.73%. The Greywolf Capital Management Lp holds 2.20M shares with $23.90 million value, down from 3.13 million last quarter. Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co now has $1.48B valuation. The stock declined 0.62% or $0.07 reaching $11.93 per share. About 322,309 shares traded. Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (NASDAQ:HMHC) has declined 25.97% since July 24, 2016 and is downtrending. It has underperformed by 42.67% the S&P500.
FreeSeas Inc. is an international dry bulk shipping company. The company has market cap of $740,139. The Firm owns approximately two Handysize dry bulk carriers and operates over four Handysize dry bulk carriers. It currently has negative earnings. The Company’s vessels carry a range of drybulk commodities, including iron ore, grain and coal, which are referred to as major bulks, as well as bauxite, phosphate, fertilizers, steel products, cement, sugar and rice, or minor bulks.
Analysts await Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (NASDAQ:HMHC) to report earnings on August, 3 before the open. They expect $-0.23 EPS, down 2,200.00% or $0.22 from last year’s $-0.01 per share. After $-0.96 actual EPS reported by Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co for the previous quarter, Wall Street now forecasts -76.04% EPS growth. 
Investors sentiment increased to 1.12 in Q4 2016. Its up 0.33, from 0.79 in 2016Q3. It improved, as 20 investors sold HMHC shares while 40 reduced holdings. 23 funds opened positions while 44 raised stakes. 119.77 million shares or 2.47% less from 122.80 million shares in 2016Q3 were reported. Mutual Of America Capital Mgmt holds 0.17% or 830,167 shares. Brown Brothers Harriman owns 200 shares or 0% of their US portfolio. Goldman Sachs Gp Inc stated it has 2.00 million shares. Nationwide Fund reported 80,334 shares. Royal Bank & Trust Of Canada accumulated 15,851 shares. Rhumbline Advisers stated it has 138,181 shares or 0% of all its holdings. Legal And General Group Inc Public Limited Company invested in 0% or 42,800 shares. Marshall Wace Llp holds 80,027 shares. Blackrock owns 76,412 shares. Blackrock Gru reported 0% stake. Ny State Common Retirement Fund owns 820,510 shares or 0.01% of their US portfolio. Manufacturers Life The holds 84,886 shares or 0% of its portfolio. Kcg Inc accumulated 0% or 18,381 shares. Principal Financial Grp Inc has 16,985 shares for 0% of their portfolio. Morgan Stanley holds 5.62M shares.
Among 4 analysts covering Houghton Mifflin Harcourt (NASDAQ:HMHC), 2 have Buy rating, 0 Sell and 2 Hold. Therefore 50% are positive. Houghton Mifflin Harcourt had 8 analyst reports since August 7, 2015 according to SRatingsIntel. As per Friday, June 23, the company rating was maintained by BMO Capital Markets. The rating was maintained by Oppenheimer on Friday, August 7 with “Buy”. The company was initiated on Monday, October 5 by Wells Fargo. Citigroup maintained Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (NASDAQ:HMHC) on Wednesday, August 17 with “Buy” rating. The stock of Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (NASDAQ:HMHC) earned “Buy” rating by Citigroup on Thursday, September 10. The rating was maintained by Stifel Nicolaus with “Hold” on Monday, July 10. The stock of Houghton Mifflin Harcourt Co (NASDAQ:HMHC) earned “Strong Sell” rating by Zacks on Tuesday, August 11. The rating was downgraded by BMO Capital Markets on Friday, August 5 to “Market Perform”.








