Hear from our Team Members


‹
›





I've stayed at HMH 13+ years-my longest tenure at any company in my life-for two main reasons: 1) the amazing products and services we provide to help educate, inform, and entertain children and adults, and 2) the people who work here are passionate about what they do, interesting, collaborative, and all around good people
Jeanette





As a new employee of HMH, I have found an organization which supports you with both collegiality and congeniality to make the transition into the company a smooth one. Numerous workshops and trainings allow you to learn and access the tools you need to be successful. It is exciting to present the products to teachers and see the impact HMH resources can have on student achievement. I look forward to the opportunities ahead!
Kathy





My time at HMH has afforded me the opportunity to develop and master an array of technical and leadership skills while engaging in meaningful work. I continue to be energized by dedicated and innovative co-workers who respect each other's expertise and address challenges collaboratively.
Mary





Having been in education over 20 years I've always had interaction with HMH. A very good colleague of mine works at HMH and told me how happy she is in her job. So when the opportunity presented itself, I applied for the job. I was hired and the journey begins. What a wonderful group of people to work for and with. My mentor and colleagues have been so helpful during my new hire (35 days in). So far its been a great place to work.
Michael





I just recently got hired as an associate content specialist. I was attracted to work here because of being able to travel to new locations and meet new people.I get to work from home when I'm not traveling and when I am out of the office I get to meet with administrators and teachers promoting essential HMH curriculum products. I am engaged on a daily basis because every day is different! I am new to corporate America, but already I can tell that this is a really great company filled with genuine people.
Kelly





Working at HMH is interesting, challenging, and gratifying at the same time. The people I interact with daily are dedicated professionals. At HMH, our main focus is providing meaningful content to educate students of all ages. Who can argue with that?! I'm proud to be part of HMH and am excited about the future of our company.
David





Two things have kept me at HMH for these many years: the high quality products that I am proud to represent; and the dedicated and talented people with whom I am honored to work.
Carol





Our HMH Recruiters do a fantastic job of understanding the qualifications I'm seeking in a great candidate and they do the hard work of searching for and moving forward high quality people! Our recruiters are perceptive and responsive to my work habits and flow as they guide me through the process. First impressions are enduring. Job candidates have commented on the positive nature of their interactions with their HMH recruiter. HMH Recruiters are a winning team!
David





There are 2 major benefits to working within the HMH community. First, the level of support during on-boarding is phenomenal. There are so many people and resources available to help you be successful as soon as possible. Second, HMH wants you to grow. Consequently, there are real opportunities to learn, to explore new challenges, and advance. My first 10 months on the job have been fulfilling and I feel as though I'm contributing significantly, with a bright future ahead.
Chris





"If you like to work with educated, creative, and interesting people who are deeply invested in helping children learn, HMH is a great place to be!
                                I have worked for HMH for over 23 years and it has been a wonderful place to learn and grow. The work is constantly interesting and challenging. I also get great support, both personally and professionally, from my colleagues and managers, and the work/life balance is excellent. And finally, there is a strong culture of respect for all individuals here. Each person is valued for the unique strengths that they bring to the organization.
                                I feel very lucky to be part of a company that makes outstanding, high-quality products that help children and families and teachers navigate the learning process together.
                                One of the most exciting aspects of working for a top publisher like HMH is that we gain such valuable technical skills, since the technology of learning is constantly changing.”
Lisa





Working at HMH has been deeply fulfilling because I am able to synthesize my love for writing and education by creating materials that help improve student learning.
Nina




I love knowing that I make a difference and being able to see that the work I do, and the energy I bring to it, truly affects the lives of lifelong learners.
Jennifer





After being a per diem consultant for 15 months, I was awarded full time status as an Associate Content Specialist. The opportunities for growth and the benefits that come along with it, make working for HMH exciting and rewarding.
Lawrence





As a fairly new employee to HMH, I have always been attracted to this company. While still a French teacher, I used many of the products-both past and present-that the company offered. In addition, I have always been impressed with the level of professionalism exhibited by all HMH employees that I encountered. Now that I am a part of the HMH team, I am constantly amazed at the collaboration, willingness, and overall enthusiasm that everyone exhibits. As a part of HMH, I am not spread across several content areas. I am allowed to focus on my passion and strengths: World Languages. My colleagues, the products, and the work environment make each workday a joy!
Ricky




